# Rocket.new — Supabase Expert Reference (Web)

> Supabase is Rocket's primary backend. ~40% of all technical issues are Supabase-related.

---

## The Four Most Common Supabase Issues (In Frequency Order)

### 1. Migration Scripts Not Pushed
**Symptom**: App builds fine, data doesn't save, auth fails, or tables are missing.
**Fix**: Project → Integrations → Supabase → Migrations → Push all pending
**Why**: Rocket generates migration files but they must be applied to create the actual tables in Supabase.

### 2. Supabase Project Paused (Free Tier)
**Symptom**: App was working, now completely broken with database connection errors.
**Fix**: supabase.com → open project → click "Restore" → wait 2–3 min
**Why**: Supabase free tier auto-pauses projects after 7 days of inactivity.
**Prevention**: Upgrade Supabase to a paid tier, or keep the project active.

### 3. Redirect URLs Missing (Auth Breaks on Deploy)
**Symptom**: Auth confirmation email link fails, OAuth login loops, "invalid redirect" errors after deploying.
**Fix**: Supabase → Auth → URL Configuration → add all app URLs

Must include ALL of these:
```
http://localhost:3000
https://[your-rocket-preview-url]
https://[your-app].netlify.app
https://[your-custom-domain.com]   ← add when custom domain is connected
```

### 4. RLS Policies Missing or Wrong
**Symptom**: Authenticated users can't see their own data, or can see everyone's data.
**Fix**: Supabase → Table Editor → select table → RLS → add correct policy

Common RLS policy pattern:
```sql
-- Allow users to see their own rows
CREATE POLICY "Users can view own data"
ON table_name FOR SELECT
USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Allow users to insert their own rows
CREATE POLICY "Users can insert own data"
ON table_name FOR INSERT
WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Allow users to update their own rows
CREATE POLICY "Users can update own data"
ON table_name FOR UPDATE
USING (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

Quick Rocket fix: ask in chat "Fix the RLS policies for the [table name] table so authenticated users can read and write their own data"

