## Auth Methods Supported

| Method | Complexity | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Email + password | Low | Works out of the box |
| Magic link | Low | Passwordless, email OTP |
| Google OAuth | Medium | Google Cloud Console setup needed |
| GitHub OAuth | Medium | GitHub Developer Settings needed |
| Apple Sign In | High | Apple Developer account required |

## Social Auth Setup — Google (Step by Step)
1. **Google Cloud Console**: Create project → APIs & Services → Credentials → Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application type)
2. **Authorized JavaScript origins**: add `https://[supabase-id].supabase.co` and your app domains
3. **Authorized redirect URI**: `https://[supabase-id].supabase.co/auth/v1/callback`
4. Copy Client ID + Client Secret
5. **Supabase**: Auth → Providers → Google → paste credentials → Enable → Save
6. **Rocket**: `/Add Social Authentication with Google` or ask in chat

## Social Auth Setup — GitHub
1. GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → OAuth Apps → New OAuth App
2. Homepage URL: `https://your-app.netlify.app`
3. Authorization callback URL: `https://[supabase-id].supabase.co/auth/v1/callback`
4. Copy Client ID + Client Secret
5. **Supabase**: Auth → Providers → GitHub → paste → Enable → Save

