## Supabase Edge Functions (Serverless)

Used for: API proxying (CORS bypass), webhook handling, server-side logic, Stripe webhooks.

### When to Use Edge Functions
- External API has CORS restrictions blocking browser requests
- Need to keep secret keys server-side (not in frontend code)
- Stripe webhook signature verification (requires raw request body)
- Sending emails server-side

### CORS Proxy Pattern
```typescript
// supabase/functions/proxy/index.ts
Deno.serve(async (req) => {
  const { url, method, body } = await req.json()
  const response = await fetch(url, { method, body: JSON.stringify(body),
    headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${Deno.env.get('EXTERNAL_API_KEY')}`, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
  })
  const data = await response.json()
  return new Response(JSON.stringify(data), {
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*' }
  })
})
```

